
Regular github commands:

* mkdir - creating a directory
* git init - initializing a remote directory as a github repo
* git add . -add - files to the staging area
* git commit -m - used to commit changes on a file
* git show - used to display recently implemented changes
* ''  clone - used to get changes made in a website
* git pull - pulls the content of a git hu repo
* git push - used to push changes fro remote repository to github
* git branch - used to create a branch from main brach
* git globaluser.name"" - used to create a remote user name
* git globaluse.email "" - used to create user email
* git globalcolour "auto". -sets virtual screen color to auto
* touch - creating a new file
* vi "file name" - used in wtiring to a file
* cat "file name" - used to display file content
* clear - rubs the content of the terminal (cleans the terminal)
* git diff - used to show the newly implented changes to a file compared to the previous file.
* ls - lists content of the current directory
* pwd - print the current working directory
* cd .. - shifting from one directory to the previous dir.
* cd ../.. - shifting 2x backwards
* cd "dir name" - shifting from one directory to another.
* git status - showing the current status of files in a repository.
* wq - saving
* i - insert
* git remove - deleting a repo

